WEBVTT

00:04:14.000 --> 00:04:25.999
[Singing]

00:04:26.000 --> 00:04:35.999
[Singing]

00:04:36.000 --> 00:04:43.999
[Singing] That's right! Wow, welcome.
Here we are again on a Monday.

00:04:44.000 --> 00:04:45.999
Wait, is it Monday today? --It is.

00:04:46.000 --> 00:04:55.999
It's been a tiring day. The weekend ended, Monday
began again, and everyone must be exhausted.

00:04:56.000 --> 00:05:04.999
So PLAVE is here at exactly 8 p.m.--a
cure-all for the Monday blues.

00:05:05.000 --> 00:05:12.999
I can't get my words out. Weverse user
'Gulping Down Water' is here with us too.

00:05:13.000 --> 00:05:22.999
So many PLLI are chatting--calling us princes and
saying 'ppyong.' The response is very enthusiastic.

00:05:23.000 --> 00:05:27.999
That's right. Shall we start
with a little casual chatting?

00:05:28.000 --> 00:05:34.999
Yesterday was the weekend, so let's briefly
tell each other how we spent Saturday.

00:05:35.000 --> 00:05:42.999
Well, I watched the World Cup final. You all watched the
whole final, right? --I did. It was early this morning.

00:05:43.000 --> 00:05:50.999
Right. Our group chat was very lively early this
morning. We wanted to chat with PLLI too, but...

00:05:51.000 --> 00:05:58.999
it was around 4 a.m., and messages might have woken
people who weren't watching, so the PLAVE members...

00:05:59.000 --> 00:06:05.999
talked among ourselves instead. It was a thrilling
match, and we even made a bet. --We did.

00:06:06.000 --> 00:06:07.999
I was the only one who got it right.

00:06:08.000 --> 00:06:15.999
Right. We bet a meal--Korean
beef--and the rest of us lost.

00:06:16.000 --> 00:06:18.999
Our predictions missed the mark.

00:06:19.000 --> 00:06:28.999
I meant to watch to the end, but late in the second
half--around the 40-minute mark--my memory just stops.

00:06:29.000 --> 00:06:29.999
Oh, you fell asleep.

00:06:30.000 --> 00:06:36.999
I was exhausted. At kickoff we all said, 'Let's
make it through 45 minutes,' but Yejun-hyung...

00:06:37.000 --> 00:06:41.999
At some point, the unread '1' beside our KakaoTalk
messages stopped disappearing. --Right, right.

00:06:42.000 --> 00:06:50.999
At 4 a.m. we were all posting proof photos and
asking, 'What are you doing? Is everyone ready?'

00:06:51.000 --> 00:06:54.999
I didn't see the whole thing. How far
did you two watch? Did you finish it?

00:06:55.000 --> 00:07:02.999
I watched everything--the ceremony, the
medals, and the trophy being lifted.

00:07:03.000 --> 00:07:10.999
I kept drifting in and out because I was so tired,
even with all the tension and excitement of a final.

00:07:11.000 --> 00:07:18.999
Right? I was tense too, but around the second
half I relaxed and ended up falling asleep.

00:07:19.000 --> 00:07:22.999
So, yes--I lost the bet.

00:07:23.000 --> 00:07:27.999
I was confident because I had
a very strong prediction.

00:07:28.000 --> 00:07:30.999
Of course, no result is ever
guaranteed during a match.

00:07:31.000 --> 00:07:34.999
Still, I think my prediction
shone a little today.

00:07:35.000 --> 00:07:41.999
So now we have to buy Eunho Korean beef. Someone is
asking if we're splitting the cost evenly. --No.

00:07:42.000 --> 00:07:44.999
Of course not. We have to make
it winner-takes-all again.

00:07:45.000 --> 00:07:48.999
We'll probably need another bet.
--Winner takes all? --Obviously.

00:07:49.000 --> 00:07:56.999
People are asking which country
won. Spain beat Argentina 1–0.

00:07:57.000 --> 00:08:00.999
I'm actually a huge Messi fan.

00:08:01.000 --> 00:08:08.999
You really like Messi. Seeing how
disappointed he looked was quite moving.

00:08:09.000 --> 00:08:16.999
I heard he shed tears too. I have enormous respect
for him still excelling at the World Cup at his age.

00:08:17.000 --> 00:08:21.999
I hope he keeps doing great
things. He was incredible.

00:08:22.000 --> 00:08:29.999
And I'm a huge fan of Lamine Yamal.

00:08:30.000 --> 00:08:33.999
He's receiving attention
from all over the world.

00:08:34.000 --> 00:08:40.999
Right. Yamal is extremely young--only nineteen.

00:08:41.000 --> 00:08:48.999
Years ago, when Messi was about twenty,
he bathed baby Yamal for a photo shoot.

00:08:49.000 --> 00:08:56.999
It became famous. Meeting again twenty years
later in a World Cup final feels like a movie.

00:08:57.000 --> 00:09:04.999
After the match, Messi was sitting
there, and Yamal came over to him.

00:09:05.000 --> 00:09:10.999
Twenty years ago, Messi was the
one holding him in his arms.

00:09:11.000 --> 00:09:18.999
This time Yamal approached and embraced
Messi first. It was really moving.

00:09:19.000 --> 00:09:24.999
Right, that was another emotional
moment. Yamal was only a baby back then.

00:09:25.000 --> 00:09:33.999
Apparently he was six months old. Messi was
twenty and already at the top of the sport.

00:09:34.000 --> 00:09:41.999
Then Yamal grew into a world-class player too,
and they met again as equals on the field.

00:09:42.000 --> 00:09:45.999
That embrace was more cinematic
than an actual movie.

00:09:46.000 --> 00:09:53.999
Exactly. They weren't an adult and a baby anymore,
but two players showing each other sportsmanship.

00:09:54.000 --> 00:09:59.999
And while we're talking about football,
we can't leave out the halftime show.

00:10:00.000 --> 00:10:02.999
I nearly cried then.

00:10:03.000 --> 00:10:07.999
Justin Bieber sunbaenim was so amazing
that I fell for him all over again.

00:10:08.000 --> 00:10:09.999
That lineup was unbelievable.

00:10:10.000 --> 00:10:17.999
He performed the World Cup version of 'Hallelujah.' It
gave me goosebumps--just his voice and an acoustic guitar.

00:10:18.000 --> 00:10:19.999
One voice and one acoustic guitar. --Right.

00:10:20.000 --> 00:10:28.999
He entered like one of the players, wearing
something with 'JB' on it--his initials.

00:10:29.000 --> 00:10:37.999
He listened to the stage directions,
walked straight in, and began. Wow.

00:10:38.000 --> 00:10:44.999
My English isn't good enough to understand every lyric, but
the general message was about everyone celebrating together.

00:10:45.000 --> 00:10:53.999
It felt like a blessing for everyone--happy and
uplifting, and perfectly suited to the World Cup.

00:10:54.000 --> 00:11:00.999
At the end he changed it to a World Cup
refrain, and I got goosebumps all over.

00:11:01.000 --> 00:11:07.999
And then BTS sunbaenim appeared
among that incredible lineup--wow.

00:11:08.000 --> 00:11:16.999
[Sings briefly] Sorry, I don't
know the lyrics very well.

00:11:17.000 --> 00:11:29.999
Watching the 'Dynamite' stage filled me with so
much pride in Korea. Is it okay to say that?

00:11:30.000 --> 00:11:36.999
I was overflowing with it--with patriotism.

00:11:37.000 --> 00:11:40.999
I honestly almost cried. I was so overwhelmed.

00:11:41.000 --> 00:11:47.999
Since Hamin brought it up, I suddenly want
to say that Ppongtta is my favorite ice pop.

00:11:48.000 --> 00:11:56.999
All that patriotism made you think of
ice cream? So you like Ppongtta. --Yes.

00:11:57.000 --> 00:11:57.999
Nice, nice. I like it.

00:11:58.000 --> 00:12:03.999
People are mentioning Bburinkle in the comments. The
uncanny thing is, I watched while eating Bburinkle chicken.

00:12:04.000 --> 00:12:15.999
I ordered it around 3 a.m., but it arrived
an hour and a half later, around halftime.

00:12:16.000 --> 00:12:22.999
At least you still got to enjoy it
during the match. Wow, but then...

00:12:23.000 --> 00:12:32.999
Chicken-shop owners must have worked through the night.
Few places were open, so orders probably piled up.

00:12:33.000 --> 00:12:38.999
It arrived a little cold, but sharing it
with the World Cup was still a lot of fun.

00:12:39.000 --> 00:12:46.999
I ate chicken too. I bought frozen dakgangjeong in
advance because I expected huge delivery delays.

00:12:47.000 --> 00:12:49.999
I wanted to show my patriotism,
so I chose Schnell Chicken.

00:12:50.000 --> 00:12:57.999
Schnell Chicken is closely associated with that feeling.
As a proud citizen of Asterum, I had to eat it.

00:12:58.000 --> 00:13:04.999
The package even lists a 'veteran' method and an
'active-duty' method. Which did you use? --Active-duty.

00:13:05.000 --> 00:13:12.999
He chose the active-duty version while watching
the players still out there competing.

00:13:13.000 --> 00:13:14.999
What did you have as your World Cup food?

00:13:15.000 --> 00:13:22.999
I had musaengchae. --So you ate radish salad.

00:13:23.000 --> 00:13:29.999
Yes, musaengchae and... --Only musaengchae?
That must have made quite a snack.

00:13:30.000 --> 00:13:34.999
No, no, that's not what I mean. Musaengchae
was simply all I had in the fridge.

00:13:35.000 --> 00:13:45.999
You sent us a photo after seeing it on the
livestream. --Was it in a yogurt bowl? --No, no.

00:13:46.000 --> 00:13:47.999
You were having musaengchae with cola.

00:13:48.000 --> 00:13:59.999
The cola went down nicely. Some PLLI watched the match
and others slept, but it was a tense, thrilling game.

00:14:00.000 --> 00:14:12.999
Now let's move on from the World Cup and
talk about how we spent the weekend.

00:14:13.000 --> 00:14:18.999
I'm having trouble reading this right
now. --Wow, you did a lot of work.

00:14:19.000 --> 00:14:26.999
One on Monday, one on Tuesday, one on Wednesday,
one on Thursday, one on Friday, then the weekend...

00:14:27.000 --> 00:14:29.999
Right? --Yes. One item on Monday.

00:14:30.000 --> 00:14:32.999
And one on Tuesday.

00:14:33.000 --> 00:14:37.999
Yesterday we all gathered and worked
on something together. --That's right.

00:14:38.000 --> 00:14:46.999
We finished near dawn, but we
prepared another gift for PLLI.

00:14:47.000 --> 00:14:47.999
We did.

00:14:48.000 --> 00:14:50.999
And you bought a new pair of slippers yesterday.

00:14:51.000 --> 00:14:54.999
Yes, I bought new slippers. --What
prompted that change in footwear?

00:14:55.000 --> 00:15:02.999
I used to wear really thick shoes,
and then I switched to flip-flops.

00:15:03.000 --> 00:15:07.999
You know the other pair--the
black flip-flops. --Right.

00:15:08.000 --> 00:15:15.999
I looked at them and wondered, what
do you call this part of a flip-flop?

00:15:16.000 --> 00:15:18.999
The part that goes between your toes.

00:15:19.000 --> 00:15:26.999
What is that piece called? You know that
curved toe strap? It looked so sad.

00:15:27.000 --> 00:15:28.999
Like it was crying.

00:15:29.000 --> 00:15:33.999
Exactly. I kept getting the feeling
that my flip-flops were crying.

00:15:34.000 --> 00:15:43.999
So I decided they needed a friend and
bought another pretty black pair.

00:15:44.000 --> 00:15:47.999
They look very sturdy and
cushioned. --They really are soft.

00:15:48.000 --> 00:15:54.999
It surprised us too, so we hurried to tell everyone
on Bubble. I hope that clears up the mystery.

00:15:55.000 --> 00:15:57.999
And I went exploring restaurants
with Noah-hyung. --Restaurants?

00:15:58.000 --> 00:16:04.999
I thought it might be fun to visit a favorite
restaurant with each member in turn.

00:16:05.000 --> 00:16:14.999
I reached Noah-hyung first, so we went out for some
good food. There were raw chicken feet on the table.

00:16:15.000 --> 00:16:15.999
Raw chicken feet?

00:16:16.000 --> 00:16:19.999
I honestly thought they were kimchi and
put one in my mouth. --A raw chicken foot?

00:16:20.000 --> 00:16:24.999
Yes. It looked so much like
kimchi that I didn't think twice.

00:16:25.000 --> 00:16:26.999
Then I realized with a shock that I had
put a raw chicken foot in my mouth.

00:16:27.000 --> 00:16:32.999
I didn't swallow it. I put it in, went, 'What is
this?' and took it out. Noah-hyung laughed a lot.

00:16:33.000 --> 00:16:39.999
So you went out for chicken feet?
--We went for grilled chicken.

00:16:40.000 --> 00:16:47.999
Salt-grilled, marinated, and so on. We ordered one
serving of chicken feet too, and that happened.

00:16:48.000 --> 00:16:55.999
Next, I'd like each member to share a favorite
place and go on a one-on-one food date with me.

00:16:56.000 --> 00:16:58.999
Yes, give it some thought.

00:16:59.000 --> 00:17:08.999
I'm already planning one tailored to Eunho. And I'm
really looking forward to Yejun-hyung's. --I'm confident.

00:17:09.000 --> 00:17:15.999
So you're preparing some exciting content. --That's
right. And we've had a lot of rain lately.

00:17:16.000 --> 00:17:16.999
Sing us the line you were singing earlier.

00:17:17.000 --> 00:17:20.999
[Sings briefly]

00:17:21.000 --> 00:17:27.999
It rained so much. I passed a stream the
other day--an actual stream of water.

00:17:28.000 --> 00:17:29.999
The water was overflowing its banks.

00:17:30.000 --> 00:17:32.999
It rained enough to submerge the whole track.

00:17:33.000 --> 00:17:37.999
Lightning was crashing too. Were you all
right? --It came during the night. --Right.

00:17:38.000 --> 00:17:42.999
They originally said the heavy rain would
last through Sunday--or was it Saturday?

00:17:43.000 --> 00:17:45.999
They said through Saturday, but
didn't it stop raining on Saturday?

00:17:46.000 --> 00:17:53.999
Weather is so changeable that you never know what will
happen. I sincerely hope nobody suffered serious damage.

00:17:54.000 --> 00:18:01.999
I went outside during the lightning in the middle of
the night. --Really? Why? --To stand in the rain.

00:18:02.000 --> 00:18:08.999
I shouted as if even lightning would avoid me.
--Did you have an appointment with the storm?

00:18:09.000 --> 00:18:12.999
No, I just yelled, 'Come
at me, world! Come at me!'

00:18:13.000 --> 00:18:19.999
Nobody could file a noise complaint because the thunder
covered my shouting. This won't show up in a reel, will it?

00:18:20.000 --> 00:18:24.999
Maybe we'll encounter it in a Reel or
a Short someday. --No, that wasn't it.

00:18:25.000 --> 00:18:30.999
There is romance in quietly standing in the
rain, but please be careful not to catch a cold.

00:18:31.000 --> 00:18:34.999
Everyone has favorite items
they use only when it rains.

00:18:35.000 --> 00:18:38.999
Do you have one--an umbrella, rain
boots, a raincoat, something like that?

00:18:39.000 --> 00:18:42.999
For me, it was actually flip-flops.

00:18:43.000 --> 00:18:46.999
Whenever it rained, I always wore
flip-flops. My feet would get wet anyway.

00:18:47.000 --> 00:18:50.999
I don't really like wearing
sneakers in the rain. --Really?

00:18:51.000 --> 00:18:54.999
They get completely soaked,
and I hate that feeling.

00:18:55.000 --> 00:19:02.999
Flip-flops let my feet dry quickly, though they
can be dangerous. I made sure to wash mine.

00:19:03.000 --> 00:19:05.999
Flip-flops get slippery. --Right, right.

00:19:06.000 --> 00:19:11.999
You never know what your feet might do.
Eunho, do you have a favorite rainy-day item?

00:19:12.000 --> 00:19:19.999
For rainy days? Pajeon. --You went
straight to food. Pajeon is great.

00:19:20.000 --> 00:19:21.999
Kimchi pancakes, potato
pancakes--all kinds of jeon.

00:19:22.000 --> 00:19:27.999
That's all I can think about when it rains.

00:19:28.000 --> 00:19:34.999
Bossam, pajeon, every kind of
jeon... or perhaps horror movies.

00:19:35.000 --> 00:19:39.999
Horror movies, right. But you
don't usually enjoy them.

00:19:40.000 --> 00:19:45.999
They aren't fun when there's no story. --No, you
just haven't seen horror movies with good stories.

00:19:46.000 --> 00:19:53.999
I don't care much for simple ghost stories, but
I love frightening stories with a strong plot.

00:19:54.000 --> 00:20:00.999
The atmosphere can be overwhelming. For example, there's
a film whose title was recognized unclearly here.

00:20:01.000 --> 00:20:09.999
It isn't supernatural horror so much as the fear
that something like this could happen in real life.

00:20:10.000 --> 00:20:18.999
I really recommend it. Even people who struggle
with scary films might enjoy the story.

00:20:19.000 --> 00:20:19.999
Oh. Okay.

00:20:20.000 --> 00:20:24.999
Keep it in mind and watch it
sometime. It's worth seeing.

00:20:25.000 --> 00:20:30.999
It may look frightening at first, but it
isn't very scary and has few jump scares.

00:20:31.000 --> 00:20:38.999
I recommend it. For me, rainy
days make me think of a football.

00:20:39.000 --> 00:20:46.999
I've played football with friends in the rain
since childhood--what I call 'water football.'

00:20:47.000 --> 00:20:55.999
I like playing in the rain, and lately I love running
in it too. --You really do. Sports help you unwind.

00:20:56.000 --> 00:21:00.999
I, on the other hand, love
staying home when it rains.

00:21:01.000 --> 00:21:09.999
Rather than going out, I shower, turn
the air conditioning down cold...

00:21:10.000 --> 00:21:15.999
and curl up under one of those smooth, fluffy
blankets. What is that material called?

00:21:16.000 --> 00:21:22.999
Not a warm fabric, but one that feels cool. You
know what I mean--I can't remember the word.

00:21:23.000 --> 00:21:27.999
I love covering myself with one. --Me too.

00:21:28.000 --> 00:21:33.999
I hope PLLI can find happiness in
rainy days in your own way too.

00:21:34.000 --> 00:21:40.999
And again, please be careful during the rainy
season and typhoons. We hope you avoid any damage.

00:21:41.000 --> 00:21:44.999
It's midsummer now, so we'll
probably get much more rain.

00:21:45.000 --> 00:21:49.999
Right. And once the rain passes,
please be careful in the heat as well.

00:21:50.000 --> 00:21:52.999
Now, Bamby-hyung had his birthday livestream.

00:21:53.000 --> 00:22:00.999
Did you all watch it? --Of course. What stood
out most? --The dance with the hamsters.

00:22:01.000 --> 00:22:01.999
Yes, during 'BÆD.'

00:22:02.000 --> 00:22:06.999
Was the hamster dance during
'BÆD'? I think it was.

00:22:07.000 --> 00:22:09.999
The hamsters danced with him.

00:22:10.000 --> 00:22:17.999
My friends asked me, 'How do hamsters
dance?' I don't know either.

00:22:18.000 --> 00:22:20.999
How would I know? None of us knows.

00:22:21.000 --> 00:22:24.999
They moved, but they looked a little soulless.

00:22:25.000 --> 00:22:27.999
Like that blank, battery-powered
kind of movement?

00:22:28.000 --> 00:22:29.999
Something like that. But they were cute.

00:22:30.000 --> 00:22:31.999
They were extremely cute.

00:22:32.000 --> 00:22:40.999
And turning the clock hands to exactly 12:32
was adorable. But there was a secret behind it.

00:22:41.000 --> 00:22:41.999
A secret? What secret?

00:22:42.000 --> 00:22:45.999
One complete turn of the hand should
advance the clock by an hour.

00:22:46.000 --> 00:22:53.999
But it took two turns to advance one hour.
What could those two turns have meant?

00:22:54.000 --> 00:22:56.999
What? Was it three? We don't really know either.

00:22:57.000 --> 00:23:04.999
It took two rotations for an hour to pass. Whenever we
say anything, PLLI asks if it's a spoiler. We wonder too.

00:23:05.000 --> 00:23:05.999
Right.

00:23:06.000 --> 00:23:13.999
You sang that song beautifully, and you
also sang a pop song. --Right, right.

00:23:14.000 --> 00:23:23.999
Bamby-hyung worked very hard, finding time in our
busy schedule to prepare things to show everyone.

00:23:24.000 --> 00:23:29.999
Didn't you do that routine before singing the
first song during the birthday live? --Yes.

00:23:30.000 --> 00:23:37.999
[Quotes a line] When you
get extremely nervous...

00:23:38.000 --> 00:23:45.999
there's that routine where you tremble like a
frightened hamster. PLLI found it adorable.

00:23:46.000 --> 00:23:51.999
That is actually where the emotion begins.
You have to immerse yourself in it.

00:23:52.000 --> 00:24:00.999
Then you deliver the song with feeling.
Anyway, happy birthday again, Bamby-hyung.

00:24:01.000 --> 00:24:08.999
We celebrated him. And besides Bamby's live, the members
ate cup ramen together for the first time in ages.

00:24:09.000 --> 00:24:15.999
'Ramen, come to me!' Noah-hyung pretended not
to care until his true intentions were exposed.

00:24:16.000 --> 00:24:20.999
That only makes you look more desperate. You
should be honest from the beginning. --Exactly.

00:24:21.000 --> 00:24:26.999
You have to eat it confidently. I still remember Yejun-hyung
boldly getting us started. --And deliciously so.

00:24:27.000 --> 00:24:35.999
I suddenly said, 'Forget it, I'm going in,' ripped
the lid back, and everyone followed: 'Me too!'

00:24:36.000 --> 00:24:38.999
That was refreshingly decisive.
Which ramen did you put in, hyung?

00:24:39.000 --> 00:24:41.999
I think mine was Shin Ramyun. Wasn't it?

00:24:42.000 --> 00:24:44.999
It was Shin. That's the only kind hyung eats.

00:24:45.000 --> 00:24:50.999
I only eat the original. You went in so decisively
that I immediately opened my Saeutang cup too.

00:24:51.000 --> 00:24:58.999
What did everyone have? --Saeutang. --I
think I had a small spicy Jin Ramen.

00:24:59.000 --> 00:25:06.999
The small one. The small cups taste
better. I love small cup noodles.

00:25:07.000 --> 00:25:15.999
Small Yukgaejang cups are legendary. Don't get the large
one--eat two small ones. They're practically different ramen.

00:25:16.000 --> 00:25:17.999
That's genuinely true of Yukgaejang too.

00:25:18.000 --> 00:25:20.999
It is fascinating. Why do the small
and large versions taste different?

00:25:21.000 --> 00:25:28.999
The noodles differ--their thickness. That's what I've heard
about bowl noodles and cup noodles, though I may be wrong.

00:25:29.000 --> 00:25:34.999
The smaller bowl version uses different noodles.
Even the names differ: bowl noodles and cup noodles.

00:25:35.000 --> 00:25:39.999
So that's the secret. But
again, I could be wrong.

00:25:40.000 --> 00:25:43.999
Really? --Yes, apparently
it's the noodle thickness.

00:25:44.000 --> 00:25:51.999
Perhaps the smaller cup needs finer
noodles to fit. Anyway, PLLI...

00:25:52.000 --> 00:25:56.999
I recommend cup ramen whenever
you need a boost. Just go for it.

00:25:57.000 --> 00:26:03.999
Especially after getting soaked in rain or playing
in water, that hot, salty broth tastes amazing.

00:26:04.000 --> 00:26:13.999
When you get the chance to eat cup ramen, don't overthink
it. It's a snack--follow your heart and eat it.

00:26:14.000 --> 00:26:14.999
Just eat it.

00:26:15.000 --> 00:26:20.999
But since debuting as PLAVE...

00:26:21.000 --> 00:26:28.999
I used to consider cup ramen far too light to
count as a meal--just a little side snack.

00:26:29.000 --> 00:26:38.999
It was so insignificant I'd forget I'd eaten it.
But Noah-hyung pays close attention to calories.

00:26:39.000 --> 00:26:46.999
So my perception changed. Eating cup ramen began to
feel like eating some enormous amount of junk food.

00:26:47.000 --> 00:26:53.999
It made me feel as if I'd done something wrong--as
though I should eat it only once a month.

00:26:54.000 --> 00:26:56.999
That's how it feels now.

00:26:57.000 --> 00:27:05.999
Being on a diet creates some unavoidable pressure,
though realistically it isn't that large a portion.

00:27:06.000 --> 00:27:09.999
Once I get hooked on ramen, I keep
eating it. I'm fine with that.

00:27:10.000 --> 00:27:13.999
Then which do you prefer:
stovetop ramen or cup ramen?

00:27:14.000 --> 00:27:18.999
At home, stovetop ramen. Anywhere
outside the house, cup ramen.

00:27:19.000 --> 00:27:23.999
What about those ramen cookers by the Han River?

00:27:24.000 --> 00:27:26.999
Even there, I'd choose cup ramen
instead of Han River ramen.

00:27:27.000 --> 00:27:30.999
Because it isn't home. --Cup ramen? Really?

00:27:31.000 --> 00:27:31.999
For me, stovetop ramen.

00:27:32.000 --> 00:27:36.999
Stovetop ramen anywhere and
everywhere. That's what I crave most.

00:27:37.000 --> 00:27:45.999
Cup ramen works as a side when you have rice or another
main dish. I also love dipping noodles in beaten egg.

00:27:46.000 --> 00:27:54.999
It feels a little like sukiyaki. I love it, but my vote
still goes to stovetop ramen. Do you stir the noodles?

00:27:55.000 --> 00:27:58.999
I actually don't stir them.
You're not supposed to.

00:27:59.000 --> 00:28:06.999
Don't break the round noodle block apart.
Keep it intact and only flip it over.

00:28:07.000 --> 00:28:12.999
Never loosen it. Let the heat cook it like
that, and the noodles stay wonderfully firm.

00:28:13.000 --> 00:28:20.999
Try it. And what about cracking an
egg on top? --I've seen that method.

00:28:21.000 --> 00:28:27.999
I think I saw a chef beat one or two eggs
and pour them over the round noodle block.

00:28:28.000 --> 00:28:30.999
That's right. I've tried it too.

00:28:31.000 --> 00:28:36.999
Talking about ramen makes me want some. I've cooked it
that way since I was three. --Since you were three?

00:28:37.000 --> 00:28:46.999
I should patent it. --You weren't born in a
convenience store. But how do you cook the egg?

00:28:47.000 --> 00:28:54.999
I usually stir it in completely. Do you
leave it soft-poached inside the ramen...

00:28:55.000 --> 00:29:01.999
or mix it through the broth like
egg-drop soup? --It depends on my mood.

00:29:02.000 --> 00:29:08.999
I like it poached, so the yolk spreads when you
lift it out and break it. That's delicious.

00:29:09.000 --> 00:29:16.999
I also like 'cloud egg': stir it, move the noodles
aside, and let the egg spread through the broth.

00:29:17.000 --> 00:29:25.999
It feels like ramen from a PC café. You know many
methods. --I clearly love ramen. I've eaten plenty of it.

00:29:26.000 --> 00:29:32.999
I used to think stirring the egg into the
broth was practically illegal. --Why?

00:29:33.000 --> 00:29:39.999
An unacceptable way to assemble ramen?
--I'm firmly on team poached egg.

00:29:40.000 --> 00:29:46.999
The textbook method. But mixing the egg through
is tasty too--it turns the broth into egg soup.

00:29:47.000 --> 00:29:51.999
Right. It becomes mild and clean,
with that egg-broth flavor.

00:29:52.000 --> 00:30:00.999
PLLI's comments overwhelmingly favor poached eggs,
though we also have mixed eggs and cloud eggs.

00:30:01.000 --> 00:30:06.999
Ramen with the egg mixed through
really can be delicious.

00:30:07.000 --> 00:30:16.999
Especially with green-onion kimchi so ripe
that you wonder if it has gone too far.

00:30:17.000 --> 00:30:19.999
Green-onion kimchi is incredible.
Is it legal? --Completely legal.

00:30:20.000 --> 00:30:27.999
It's legal, but green-onion kimchi pairs even better
with Chapagetti than with soup ramen. --True.

00:30:28.000 --> 00:30:36.999
Those two are best friends. One last suggestion:
pour the egg into the gaps between the noodles.

00:30:37.000 --> 00:30:46.999
If you keep the round block intact, there are little
gaps. Let the egg seep into and set between them.

00:30:47.000 --> 00:30:53.999
Let the egg penetrate the noodles and try it. --Do
you loosen the block afterward? --No, keep it intact.

00:30:54.000 --> 00:30:55.999
Boil it for about three or four minutes.

00:30:56.000 --> 00:31:03.999
When you can see that the egg white has
turned white and set, switch off the heat.

00:31:04.000 --> 00:31:05.999
Right.

00:31:06.000 --> 00:31:10.999
There are so many creative
ramen recipes on social media.

00:31:11.000 --> 00:31:17.999
People turn it into stir-fried noodles or even something
like a pancake. I hope you try different methods.

00:31:18.000 --> 00:31:26.999
Bamby eats his as watery as Pyeongyang naengmyeon.
Maybe that is the true 'Han River ramen.'

00:31:27.000 --> 00:31:32.999
The other day, I made one cup so
the two of us could share it.

00:31:33.000 --> 00:31:41.999
I normally fill mine slightly below the water line
so the broth stays salty--never crossing the line.

00:31:42.000 --> 00:31:44.999
Never crossing the line? Then
you crossed it with Bamby's cup.

00:31:45.000 --> 00:31:47.999
He crossed the line. He went far beyond it.

00:31:48.000 --> 00:31:54.999
He threw a fit, saying, 'There's too
much water. I'm not eating this.'

00:31:55.000 --> 00:32:03.999
I adjusted the water because he refused it. Since you crossed
the line, please apologize on the next stream. --Apologize!

00:32:04.000 --> 00:32:10.999
And we cannot skip the most important video released
over the weekend. The timing is perfect--it's 8:30.

00:32:11.000 --> 00:32:16.999
Exactly the right time. I'm a J,
so I have to keep to the schedule.

00:32:17.000 --> 00:32:21.999
Now it's finally time to review
the 'Meccha Suki' video.

00:32:22.000 --> 00:32:28.999
The response was hot, still is hot,
and will remain hot--just like ramen.

00:32:29.000 --> 00:32:31.999
How did you feel when
'Meccha Suki' was released?

00:32:32.000 --> 00:32:36.999
It felt great. We first watched it together
three or four days before release.

00:32:37.000 --> 00:32:45.999
Right. We watched it on a
small phone screen together.

00:32:46.000 --> 00:32:51.999
Even then, we kept saying how funny and well made
it was, and that PLLI would probably love it.

00:32:52.000 --> 00:32:53.999
We watched it with smiles, so
let's enjoy it together now.

00:32:54.000 --> 00:32:58.999
I keep refreshing the page
to check the view count.

00:32:59.000 --> 00:33:06.999
I check while eating, then again when I stand
up: refresh, confirm, and check once more.

00:33:07.000 --> 00:33:10.999
I'm monitoring it in real time.
Noah-hyung is probably doing the same.

00:33:11.000 --> 00:33:17.999
He's sensitive to view counts too. --Are you?
--Yes, I'm monitoring constantly. Let's begin.

00:33:18.000 --> 00:33:21.999
Here we go.

00:33:22.000 --> 00:33:30.999
It seizes the initiative from the very
start. Ah, this is delicious. So good.

00:33:31.000 --> 00:33:44.999
It's like a perfectly cooked cup of
ramen. Delicious. They're true princes.

00:33:45.000 --> 00:34:04.999
I really have so much to say about this.

00:34:05.000 --> 00:34:28.999
I know this scene became quite a
talking point. It was so pretty.

00:34:29.000 --> 00:34:33.999
I think this kind of
sensibility really suits PLAVE.

00:34:34.000 --> 00:34:40.999
Yejun-hyung loved it so much. --I was so
happy. PLAVE really can show every genre.

00:34:41.000 --> 00:34:52.999
The response was very enthusiastic when
we released this. And here we appear.

00:34:53.000 --> 00:35:10.999
Here we come.

00:35:11.000 --> 00:35:19.999
We're working incredibly hard here. Really hard.

00:35:20.000 --> 00:35:25.999
And here I am.

00:35:26.000 --> 00:35:37.999
I love this part too.

00:35:38.000 --> 00:35:47.999
It feels as if we'll be sucked into the
screen. We should recreate this scene later.

00:35:48.000 --> 00:35:58.999
This was so much fun to film.
I feel like I'm going to cry.

00:35:59.000 --> 00:36:10.999
They say a microphone appeared.

00:36:11.000 --> 00:36:17.999
[Singing]

00:36:18.000 --> 00:36:29.999
[Singing] This is my favorite part.

00:36:30.000 --> 00:36:41.999
We kept saying, 'We're almost there!
Keep going to the end. Don't stop.'

00:36:42.000 --> 00:36:44.999
[Singing]

00:36:45.000 --> 00:36:50.999
Did you keep your balance there? --I did.

00:36:51.000 --> 00:36:56.999
And that was 'Meccha Suki.'

00:36:57.000 --> 00:36:58.999
That cover truly deserved a round of applause.

00:36:59.000 --> 00:37:03.999
We had such a good time making and filming it.

00:37:04.000 --> 00:37:08.999
How did you feel when we first
decided to do this song?

00:37:09.000 --> 00:37:15.999
When we first heard it, did we watch the original
music video or the live performance first?

00:37:16.000 --> 00:37:21.999
I think we watched the music video first.
I remember thinking it would be fun to do.

00:37:22.000 --> 00:37:32.999
We thought PLLI would really like it, so we
said, 'Let's do this.' How was it for you?

00:37:33.000 --> 00:37:33.999
I was happy.

00:37:34.000 --> 00:37:42.999
Thinking back makes me emotional. It felt
like a melatonin dream--like I was dreaming.

00:37:43.000 --> 00:37:46.999
What you just said sounded like a top comment.

00:37:47.000 --> 00:37:52.999
I still remember Eunho-hyung saying,
'Hamin, isn't this basically your song?'

00:37:53.000 --> 00:37:55.999
He said, 'You should really
be at the center of this.'

00:37:56.000 --> 00:37:59.999
Because he did it so well.
It suited him perfectly.

00:38:00.000 --> 00:38:04.999
Exactly. Show us that once more.

00:38:05.000 --> 00:38:13.999
He captured the feeling so well. But every
member suited it, and the whole project was fun.

00:38:14.000 --> 00:38:21.999
Yejun-hyung especially loved the choreography.
He danced it in the mirror all day.

00:38:22.000 --> 00:38:26.999
He kept saying, 'This is so much fun.'

00:38:27.000 --> 00:38:32.999
We laughed while recording and filming,
and even learning it was great fun.

00:38:33.000 --> 00:38:36.999
Learning it really was so much fun.

00:38:37.000 --> 00:38:41.999
Hamin was hilarious while we learned it. The
choreography has so many details, though.

00:38:42.000 --> 00:38:46.999
We spent quite a while learning it properly
so we could bring out all those details.

00:38:47.000 --> 00:38:53.999
I remember our choreography teacher coming in,
and Hamin ended up teaching alongside them.

00:38:54.000 --> 00:38:58.999
That's right. From halfway through, I
joined in because we had so little time.

00:38:59.000 --> 00:39:06.999
There wasn't enough time to learn and teach it,
so we urgently asked another teacher to help.

00:39:07.000 --> 00:39:14.999
The request was so sudden. They had learned it all,
but understandably could still get a little confused.

00:39:15.000 --> 00:39:23.999
They had less than a day. Hamin was impressive:
he picked it up immediately and helped teach it.

00:39:24.000 --> 00:39:30.999
He taught it together with the teacher who came
to help. Afterward, I quietly went over to him...

00:39:31.000 --> 00:39:39.999
...and jokingly suggested we split the
fee fifty-fifty. I was only joking.

00:39:40.000 --> 00:39:47.999
The choreography is energetic and addictive.
Noah-hyung said something about it too:

00:39:48.000 --> 00:39:52.999
'Don't get too hung up on every detail; each
person's character needs to come through.'

00:39:53.000 --> 00:39:56.999
So we showed plenty of our own character
while matching the important parts.

00:39:57.000 --> 00:40:05.999
There are lots of highlights. Shall we replay
it and review them one by one? --Absolutely.

00:40:06.000 --> 00:40:08.999
Please play it again.

00:40:09.000 --> 00:40:12.999
Before it starts, we count
down: five, four, three...

00:40:13.000 --> 00:40:20.999
Then we have to enter immediately. That moment made me
the most nervous--you have to come in exactly right.

00:40:21.000 --> 00:40:22.999
Right. The timing was difficult.

00:40:23.000 --> 00:40:29.999
The editing fits this song so well.

00:40:30.000 --> 00:40:30.999
It was done so well.

00:40:31.000 --> 00:40:36.999
And why does yellow suit you so well? You almost
look like the principal from Crayon Shin-chan.

00:40:37.000 --> 00:40:41.999
You look so sweet--almost
like a pumpkin, somehow.

00:40:42.000 --> 00:40:44.999
Yes, exactly.

00:40:45.000 --> 00:40:52.999
Hamin looks so happy. Even the character
introductions match the original.

00:40:53.000 --> 00:41:00.999
They were so faithful that I felt as if I were
dreaming. I wondered whether it was real.

00:41:01.000 --> 00:41:12.999
But people loved it. Show us that
it wasn't a dream. Go on, show us.

00:41:13.000 --> 00:41:22.999
This was so much fun. Look here--I
love this move most of all.

00:41:23.000 --> 00:41:30.999
We're all genuinely enjoying ourselves here.

00:41:31.000 --> 00:41:38.999
There are some really striking
moves. I'm playing guitar here.

00:41:39.000 --> 00:41:41.999
What kind of feeling were you going for?

00:41:42.000 --> 00:41:46.999
Who plays guitar like that?
Show us what you did again.

00:41:47.000 --> 00:41:51.999
I played it like this, with the feeling
of that song I performed before.

00:41:52.000 --> 00:41:59.999
I wanted a wriggly, winding feel, so I improvised a change
to the choreography. I'm extremely pleased with it.

00:42:00.000 --> 00:42:02.999
My satisfaction is at its absolute peak.

00:42:03.000 --> 00:42:08.999
He really loves it. Noah-hyung is funny in
this part too. Shall we look at Noah's part?

00:42:09.000 --> 00:42:15.999
His movements are huge. He's standing right beside
Hamin, but he catches your eye immediately.

00:42:16.000 --> 00:42:25.999
Look at him. Wait, had we agreed to
shake our heads here? --No, we hadn't.

00:42:26.000 --> 00:42:32.999
We only said to keep throwing ourselves into it.
This is the feeling--everyone has their own.

00:42:33.000 --> 00:42:38.999
So that wasn't planned?
--No. It startled me too.

00:42:39.000 --> 00:42:48.999
It's more healing than feeling.
He's actually very serious.

00:42:49.000 --> 00:42:53.999
He is. Look at the lyrics--the
emotion is already there in his eyes.

00:42:54.000 --> 00:43:00.999
Look at the message in those eyes: 'Who knew I
had this side?' Doesn't it suit him perfectly?

00:43:01.000 --> 00:43:02.999
I truly didn't know you had this
side to you, hyung. --Neither did I.

00:43:03.000 --> 00:43:04.999
Exactly. I discovered it through the video.

00:43:05.000 --> 00:43:08.999
I thought hyung only had his cup-ramen
side. I never knew about this side.

00:43:09.000 --> 00:43:14.999
That yellow outfit also looks like danmuji--like
one enormous piece of pickled radish.

00:43:15.000 --> 00:43:19.999
It inspires all kinds of thoughts. My
first was simply, 'That looks delicious.'

00:43:20.000 --> 00:43:27.999
Delicious. It was cooked
perfectly. Truly excellent ramen.

00:43:28.000 --> 00:43:31.999
[Singing]

00:43:32.000 --> 00:43:39.999
This scene was so good.

00:43:40.000 --> 00:43:41.999
Getting our hands aligned here
was incredibly difficult.

00:43:42.000 --> 00:43:42.999
It really wasn't easy.

00:43:43.000 --> 00:43:51.999
Lining up the heart perfectly was so hard.

00:43:52.000 --> 00:43:56.999
This kept confusing us too. I
called it the three-stage pop.

00:43:57.000 --> 00:44:02.999
Back, forward--how many times was it? How many?

00:44:03.000 --> 00:44:06.999
This has something of a TikTok feel, doesn't it?

00:44:07.000 --> 00:44:17.999
How many was that? We did
well to match it as a pair.

00:44:18.000 --> 00:44:19.999
We did this part so many times too.

00:44:20.000 --> 00:44:29.999
So many times. My heart was really hurting.

00:44:30.000 --> 00:44:36.999
They told us to shake even harder.
Noah-hyung said to really go for it here.

00:44:37.000 --> 00:44:39.999
We put a lot of feeling into it.

00:44:40.000 --> 00:44:44.999
We really did. Wait, did I
actually make this movement?

00:44:45.000 --> 00:44:51.999
We timed it together. We filmed many separate
inserts; perhaps I took too much melatonin.

00:44:52.000 --> 00:44:57.999
I don't remember any of it. One, two,
three--meow. --Yes, we did that.

00:44:58.000 --> 00:45:01.999
Two, three... We did it so many times, but
I truly don't remember. That's fascinating.

00:45:02.000 --> 00:45:07.999
We filmed so many different things that it's
understandable not to remember. It was great fun.

00:45:08.000 --> 00:45:16.999
Bamby-hyung's consonant-heavy rap became a talking point.
People said it was a voice they'd never heard before.

00:45:17.000 --> 00:45:24.999
He captured it surprisingly well. Bamby said he
wasn't entirely satisfied with that take, though.

00:45:25.000 --> 00:45:28.999
Right. I think we even recorded it again.

00:45:29.000 --> 00:45:36.999
Actually, we didn't use the rerecording. Noah-hyung
and I insisted the original had to be used.

00:45:37.000 --> 00:45:43.999
Then my part comes in. I'm
so glad this made its debut.

00:45:44.000 --> 00:45:50.999
It feels as though I'm moving freely between
the upper and lower parts of my range.

00:45:51.000 --> 00:45:55.999
Recording it was so much fun.
Noah-hyung also said, 'That's it.'

00:45:56.000 --> 00:45:57.999
He said, 'This is the take we need,'
and that's how it ended up in the song.

00:45:58.000 --> 00:46:02.999
It was perfect. I think
this is the killing part.

00:46:03.000 --> 00:46:07.999
Even from rehearsal, we knew it fit perfectly.

00:46:08.000 --> 00:46:14.999
Before that, people called Bamby-hyung's rap
voice his spam-call voice--the spam-call rap.

00:46:15.000 --> 00:46:23.999
Yes--it sounds like he's
saying, 'No, thank you.'

00:46:24.000 --> 00:46:30.999
And then the mood suddenly changes.

00:46:31.000 --> 00:46:38.999
Wait. Yejun-hyung's expression here--pause right
when he opens up. He looks almost like a peacock.

00:46:39.000 --> 00:46:41.999
What were you thinking at that moment?

00:46:42.000 --> 00:46:50.999
I was taking in the energy, like I had just
been reborn. What kind of expression is that?

00:46:51.000 --> 00:47:03.999
I tried to bring it to life like this.

00:47:04.000 --> 00:47:04.999
And now we enter the dance break.

00:47:05.000 --> 00:47:15.999
I love this part too. I have something
musical to say: in the original song...

00:47:16.000 --> 00:47:22.999
...this phrase has no vibrato. I really liked
that sensibility. Normally, in my own style...

00:47:23.000 --> 00:47:30.999
...I might have sung it with more embellishment,
but I deliberately followed the original.

00:47:31.000 --> 00:47:43.999
I sang it straighter and without extra embellishment.
It suited this song better, so that's what I did.

00:47:44.000 --> 00:47:57.999
The dance break is so fast.

00:47:58.000 --> 00:48:04.999
He definitely sings it in his own distinctive
way. I don't know how many takes we filmed here.

00:48:05.000 --> 00:48:13.999
This really wasn't easy. Bamby looked
so embarrassed doing it over and over.

00:48:14.000 --> 00:48:15.999
It was difficult acting, and
we had a lot of failed takes.

00:48:16.000 --> 00:48:23.999
We really did. It was all in the eyes--somehow
lifeless and vivid at the same time.

00:48:24.000 --> 00:48:31.999
We added a gradual smile here,
changing it ever so slightly.

00:48:32.000 --> 00:48:41.999
Bamby was lying down while filming this,
right? He was lying there like this.

00:48:42.000 --> 00:48:42.999
I'll be Bamby.

00:48:43.000 --> 00:48:47.999
And all the other members watched him
together. --Right. We told him, 'It's okay.'

00:48:48.000 --> 00:48:55.999
We thought that would make the shot feel more alive.
If you look closely, there are four more faces here.

00:48:56.000 --> 00:48:56.999
They're all watching Bamby like this.

00:48:57.000 --> 00:49:00.999
It's like the viewpoint of a
cockroach--an insect's-eye view.

00:49:01.000 --> 00:49:06.999
Hamin's expression then was incredible.
Show PLLI how you looked at Bamby-hyung.

00:49:07.000 --> 00:49:16.999
Like this. He came right up to me
but never once looked into my eyes.

00:49:17.000 --> 00:49:18.999
He was telling us not to distract him.

00:49:19.000 --> 00:49:23.999
No, I was about to tease him, but from that
angle only the whites of my eyes were visible.

00:49:24.000 --> 00:49:30.999
At first we couldn't hold back our laughter, so there
were many failed takes. The final one came out well.

00:49:31.000 --> 00:49:38.999
This song has an exceptionally
clear dramatic progression.

00:49:39.000 --> 00:49:46.999
It pushes and pulls, turns exciting, then sad--like
a roller coaster. We're in act three now.

00:49:47.000 --> 00:49:52.999
Wait, did I walk like that? Oh,
right--the members mentioned it then.

00:49:53.000 --> 00:50:00.999
No, that's not it. Look
carefully at his exact posture.

00:50:01.000 --> 00:50:15.999
When most people walk forward slowly, their center
of gravity still moves like this. That's what I did.

00:50:16.000 --> 00:50:19.999
That's fascinating. I honestly had no idea.

00:50:20.000 --> 00:50:26.999
Looking now, your center of gravity
seems tilted slightly left. --Does it?

00:50:27.000 --> 00:50:34.999
Yes. Rather than moving straight ahead, your
whole direction is like this. That's amazing.

00:50:35.000 --> 00:50:39.999
Your right hand and right foot
move together. Are you a robot?

00:50:40.000 --> 00:50:46.999
How am I doing that? Am I built backward?
--Not exactly. This is incredible.

00:50:47.000 --> 00:50:50.999
It might be a miracle. --It is a miracle.

00:50:51.000 --> 00:50:52.999
It's a talent. A genuine talent.

00:50:53.000 --> 00:51:00.999
That's so fascinating. Even I find it
fascinating. And now it feels refreshing.

00:51:01.000 --> 00:51:08.999
The intensity is gradually building.

00:51:09.000 --> 00:51:26.999
Now for the solemn finale.

00:51:27.000 --> 00:51:34.999
Wait, that startled me. He suddenly
comes right into the camera.

00:51:35.000 --> 00:51:35.999
He comes rushing in.

00:51:36.000 --> 00:51:43.999
I filmed it as if I were going to burst
straight through the screen. --That's amazing.

00:51:44.000 --> 00:51:51.999
'I won't let go.' What a
protagonist. Incredible.

00:51:52.000 --> 00:51:55.999
His voice sounds wonderful there. Wait a moment.

00:51:56.000 --> 00:52:00.999
Why do you love this part so much?

00:52:01.000 --> 00:52:06.999
You seem to be making exactly the
same expression as Noah-hyung.

00:52:07.000 --> 00:52:12.999
Isn't that Hamin's face when he takes a half-body
bath? --Yes, that's the face. Pure bliss.

00:52:13.000 --> 00:52:20.999
I poured every last bit of
energy into this moment.

00:52:21.000 --> 00:52:28.999
Yejun-hyung--the fireworks are giving us quite a
welcome. Apparently only Noah-hyung steps forward here.

00:52:29.000 --> 00:52:29.999
Oh, you're right.

00:52:30.000 --> 00:52:33.999
Let's watch it again. I saw
PLLI commenting about this.

00:52:34.000 --> 00:52:41.999
Noah-hyung does the detail
differently. He really steps forward.

00:52:42.000 --> 00:52:49.999
I simply brought my feet together. Some
people stepped back. --Bamby-hyung and I did.

00:52:50.000 --> 00:52:58.999
I think I brought mine together too. Two of us did,
while Noah-hyung stepped forward. This is the key move.

00:52:59.000 --> 00:52:59.999
Right, exactly.

00:53:00.000 --> 00:53:06.999
It's also the most energetic moment, so I don't
think we synchronized every detail of our feet.

00:53:07.000 --> 00:53:10.999
The idea was simply to do it with
our own energy and go hardest here.

00:53:11.000 --> 00:53:18.999
Exactly. We matched the energy, but didn't
worry much about the footwork details.

00:53:19.000 --> 00:53:26.999
About me wobbling--Noah-hyung kept telling us
to do it. 'It'll be funnier if you wobble.'

00:53:27.000 --> 00:53:34.999
I think we agreed that all five of us would wobble
naturally. --Right. But everyone except Eunho...

00:53:35.000 --> 00:53:44.999
...tried not to wobble. --Why did you do that? We
said to wobble naturally. --I'm a perfectionist.

00:53:45.000 --> 00:53:46.999
When it comes to balance, I
don't want to lose control.

00:53:47.000 --> 00:53:55.999
Is that your own distinctive style too? --Yes.
--But are you actually good at balancing? --I am.

00:53:56.000 --> 00:54:03.999
Normally I do this and then take
one more step forward. Understood.

00:54:04.000 --> 00:54:06.999
But I shouldn't do it while standing still.

00:54:07.000 --> 00:54:10.999
Right. You have to move
forward while doing it. Crazy.

00:54:11.000 --> 00:54:19.999
So we've established that nobody
instructed him to wobble like that.

00:54:20.000 --> 00:54:28.999
You did it deliberately to make PLLI laugh. But it
works perfectly, especially because you're at the side.

00:54:29.000 --> 00:54:32.999
Losing your balance at the edge
completes the picture perfectly.

00:54:33.000 --> 00:54:40.999
If Bamby-hyung had wobbled in the center, it might
have distracted the eye. I was far away, though...

00:54:41.000 --> 00:54:47.999
...and instinctively adjusted my angle and path. Watch
again--that completes it. I'm correcting it throughout.

00:54:48.000 --> 00:54:50.999
Watch the back again. Hamin, you
have to give me credit for this.

00:54:51.000 --> 00:54:57.999
I find my path perfectly. Watch
Eunho-hyung find his mark.

00:54:58.000 --> 00:55:05.999
I'm far away, but I move forward and match the
angle. That's professional work. First, sideways.

00:55:06.000 --> 00:55:06.999
Exactly.

00:55:07.000 --> 00:55:09.999
And that concludes our review of 'Meccha Suki.'

00:55:10.000 --> 00:55:18.999
Many people are enjoying this challenge.
How about each of us trying a solo version?

00:55:19.000 --> 00:55:25.999
The challenge? All right, let's watch
it. You worked very hard here. --Indeed.

00:55:26.000 --> 00:55:32.999
My arms feel as if they're
going to fall off. Good.

00:55:33.000 --> 00:55:41.999
He's just warming up.

00:55:42.000 --> 00:55:45.999
I can't tell where he's looking.

00:55:46.000 --> 00:55:51.999
He isn't looking anywhere. His eyes are
merely open; he probably can't see a thing.

00:55:52.000 --> 00:56:00.999
He fought all the way to the end.
Shall we each try a solo version now?

00:56:01.000 --> 00:56:06.999
You have to maintain it to the very end. Who
should go first? --I'll go first. --Great.

00:56:07.000 --> 00:56:16.999
When I told PLLI on Bubble that I'd been
filming something, they asked for a spoiler.

00:56:17.000 --> 00:56:18.999
So I sent them this emoji.
This is what it meant.

00:56:19.000 --> 00:56:24.999
I was spoiling 'Meccha Suki.' That was probably
the day we filmed it. --Really? --Yes.

00:56:25.000 --> 00:56:31.999
I want PLLI to know once again
that it really was a spoiler.

00:56:32.000 --> 00:56:34.999
I'll go first.

00:56:35.000 --> 00:56:39.999
Yejun, please show us from
center stage. --Let's go.

00:56:40.000 --> 00:56:42.999
But wouldn't it be a shame
to do it dressed like this?

00:56:43.000 --> 00:56:53.999
Right. We should wear the proper
outfits. One, two, three!

00:56:54.000 --> 00:57:02.999
Oh, now he looks mysterious and enigmatic.

00:57:03.000 --> 00:57:17.999
Are you ready?

00:57:18.000 --> 00:57:21.999
Your energy seems a little low.

00:57:22.000 --> 00:57:29.999
Is there no beat? Can't you hear it? --I
couldn't hear it clearly. My start was weak.

00:57:30.000 --> 00:57:30.999
Okay, okay.

00:57:31.000 --> 00:57:33.999
The volume was too low. It
needs to be louder than this.

00:57:34.000 --> 00:57:36.999
Once you lose the beat,
there's no recovering it.

00:57:37.000 --> 00:57:39.999
Everyone, that isn't a weasel
on him. It's a raccoon.

00:57:40.000 --> 00:57:47.999
Could you play it through the studio
speakers too? We can't hear it well. Great.

00:57:48.000 --> 00:57:59.999
Give us the cue when you're
ready. Okay, here we go.

00:58:00.000 --> 00:58:11.999
You have to keep going all the way to the end!

00:58:12.000 --> 00:58:18.999
Keep going! You have to keep going!

00:58:19.000 --> 00:58:24.999
Wow.

00:58:25.000 --> 00:58:28.999
I think I could do that
for an hour. --Seriously?

00:58:29.000 --> 00:58:35.999
My expression shows how exhausted
I am. And that was my challenge.

00:58:36.000 --> 00:58:43.999
Now let's move on. What would you like to do?

00:58:44.000 --> 00:58:44.999
Do I have to do it too?

00:58:45.000 --> 00:58:47.999
Weren't you demonstrating on everyone's behalf?

00:58:48.000 --> 00:58:58.999
No, everyone is doing it. Shall I
go next? --Great. Time for cardio.

00:58:59.000 --> 00:59:08.999
In his own style. It looks a
little like he's cleaning windows.

00:59:09.000 --> 00:59:18.999
This is where it really begins. You
have to keep going--in your own style.

00:59:19.000 --> 00:59:26.999
He seems tired already.
This section is very long.

00:59:27.000 --> 00:59:32.999
I'm exhausted already. I'll finish
it off. My side hurts here.

00:59:33.000 --> 00:59:41.999
I'll make every angle razor-sharp. Cue!

00:59:42.000 --> 00:59:51.999
Hey, hey, hey!

00:59:52.000 --> 01:00:00.999
All the way down! It begins here!

01:00:01.000 --> 01:00:09.999
And that was my own version.

01:00:10.000 --> 01:00:15.999
We've shown you all three solo challenges now.

01:00:16.000 --> 01:00:20.999
Hamin, is that a raccoon attached to
you? --It is. Everyone, it's a raccoon.

01:00:21.000 --> 01:00:25.999
That's my beloved raccoon.
Would you like to keep it?

01:00:26.000 --> 01:00:34.999
No, thank you. Now that we're dressed like this,
perhaps we should speak more like gentlemen.

01:00:35.000 --> 01:00:42.999
Don't we look like crown princes?

01:00:43.000 --> 01:00:49.999
With that raccoon, Hamin looks
somewhat like the Northern Duke...

01:00:50.000 --> 01:00:54.999
...the kind of Northern Duke that's popular
in romance-fantasy stories these days.

01:00:55.000 --> 01:01:02.999
You may call me Captain of the Knights.
--Captain of the Knights, understood.

01:01:03.000 --> 01:01:05.999
Very well.

01:01:06.000 --> 01:01:10.999
In that case...

01:01:11.000 --> 01:01:18.999
My, who might that lovely person be?

01:01:19.000 --> 01:01:22.999
Let us follow her. Excuse me!

01:01:23.000 --> 01:01:46.999
I shall go ahead and find out. Wait here.

01:01:47.000 --> 01:01:55.999
Excuse me! Just a moment--may I have a word?

01:01:56.000 --> 01:02:02.999
Where did she go? Where is she?

01:02:03.000 --> 01:02:17.999
Where has my lady gone? My lady!

01:02:18.000 --> 01:02:22.999
I lost her.

01:02:23.000 --> 01:02:29.999
Who was that lovely person?
--In fact, I know her.

01:02:30.000 --> 01:02:31.999
Oh?

01:02:32.000 --> 01:02:35.999
Her name is PLLI.

01:02:36.000 --> 01:02:41.999
I have met that person many times, and
we share fond feelings for one another.

01:02:42.000 --> 01:02:45.999
Why would you say that?

01:02:46.000 --> 01:02:51.999
From now on, I shall be the one to
meet PLLI. --That cannot be allowed.

01:02:52.000 --> 01:03:03.999
Forgive me, but I intend to win her love.

01:03:04.000 --> 01:03:11.999
You have all lost your minds. Let
us settle this with a sword fight!

01:03:12.000 --> 01:03:19.999
Hey! The head, the head!
Okay--the Achilles tendon!

01:03:20.000 --> 01:03:29.999
Ow, ow, ow! We cannot settle it like this, so
let us hold a proper match with a referee.

01:03:30.000 --> 01:03:43.999
Let us go. Recover your strength.

01:03:44.000 --> 01:03:55.999
Swish, swish, swish.

01:03:56.000 --> 01:04:01.999
For this purpose, I have prepared a Nintendo.

01:04:02.000 --> 01:04:10.999
A Nintendo? Surely my victory is a foregone
conclusion. --Is it? Then face me.

01:04:11.000 --> 01:04:20.999
Kicking aside, I am unrivaled with a sword.
Today I shall practice 'tae-kum-do.'

01:04:21.000 --> 01:04:25.999
Come at me. --Very well. --Let me join too.

01:04:26.000 --> 01:04:30.999
All right, wait. It isn't
your turn yet. --Understood.

01:04:31.000 --> 01:04:40.999
Die! --Understood. --I meant die in the
game! You're more ruthless than I expected.

01:04:41.000 --> 01:04:44.999
Let us begin. Do you know
the rules of this game?

01:04:45.000 --> 01:04:53.999
You play by instinct. Games
are all about instinct.

01:04:54.000 --> 01:04:59.999
Set it up. Hurry and set it up. Thank you.

01:05:00.000 --> 01:05:02.999
Do you not know how to set it up?

01:05:03.000 --> 01:05:11.999
Ow! The head! The side! The head!

01:05:12.000 --> 01:05:18.999
As expected, 'tae-kum-do' will not
suffice. Send in my next opponent.

01:05:19.000 --> 01:05:27.999
I'll go in now. --It's best of
three? So there is a second round.

01:05:28.000 --> 01:05:43.999
Okay, get ready.

01:05:44.000 --> 01:05:48.999
I gave you a handicap. Come
at me. --Okay, come on.

01:05:49.000 --> 01:05:56.999
I shall fight using only
my left hand. Third round.

01:05:57.000 --> 01:06:06.999
Press it. One hand is more
than enough. The head!

01:06:07.000 --> 01:06:14.999
The side, then the head.
You are no match for me.

01:06:15.000 --> 01:06:18.999
Begone, you sham swordsman!

01:06:19.000 --> 01:06:25.999
Next opponent, come forth. Even a
toy sword becomes real in my hands.

01:06:26.000 --> 01:06:31.999
You can only retreat. Do you
know the art of drawing a sword?

01:06:32.000 --> 01:06:39.999
Clang, clang. Set it up quickly. Are you ready?

01:06:40.000 --> 01:06:46.999
Ready. I shall face you left-handed as well.

01:06:47.000 --> 01:06:51.999
Ready? Okay, press it.

01:06:52.000 --> 01:06:58.999
Up, up, up! I told you the left and
right controls seemed reversed.

01:06:59.000 --> 01:07:07.999
You're holding it backward.
--Am I? All right, ready.

01:07:08.000 --> 01:07:23.999
Begin!

01:07:24.000 --> 01:07:34.999
A close match. Nice.

01:07:35.000 --> 01:07:43.999
Let's go! I can't attack. Press it.

01:07:44.000 --> 01:07:52.999
No, no! I lost a round. That was the handicap.

01:07:53.000 --> 01:08:00.999
I am the Melatonin Knight. A
knight eats at the knights' diner.

01:08:01.000 --> 01:08:06.999
I'll become a knight today.
Defeat this hyung--press it!

01:08:07.000 --> 01:08:12.999
Understood. It isn't responding.

01:08:13.000 --> 01:08:20.999
The head! The head!

01:08:21.000 --> 01:08:28.999
The head--wait, he's attacking!

01:08:29.000 --> 01:08:39.999
He's attacking! No! Hey!

01:08:40.000 --> 01:08:43.999
The head! You are fighting remarkably hard.

01:08:44.000 --> 01:08:47.999
The head--wait. This has descended into chaos.

01:08:48.000 --> 01:08:55.999
Wait a moment. You're working
incredibly hard. I lost badly.

01:08:56.000 --> 01:08:59.999
I am the Melatonin Knight. As a
knight, I eat at the knights' diner.

01:09:00.000 --> 01:09:08.999
I feel as if I'll fall asleep. Melatonin
Knight, I won't let you get away with this.

01:09:09.000 --> 01:09:18.999
Melatonin Knight, one pork set meal,
tofu stew, and extra Spam, please.

01:09:19.000 --> 01:09:24.999
It seems I was dreaming. Even
so, we must finish our match.

01:09:25.000 --> 01:09:31.999
I may have lost yesterday, but
today I shall win. Where were we?

01:09:32.000 --> 01:09:39.999
My eyes appear to be in quite a state.

01:09:40.000 --> 01:09:41.999
Wait. Play it again.

01:09:42.000 --> 01:09:45.999
I shall play once more.

01:09:46.000 --> 01:09:57.999
Who are you really?

01:09:58.000 --> 01:10:03.999
PLLI, listen carefully. This is
not a dream. This is reality.

01:10:04.000 --> 01:10:12.999
You seem closer to a reporter than a knight.
Which newspaper are you from? --I don't know.

01:10:13.000 --> 01:10:15.999
Just feel it, PLLI. Simply feel it.
That's all today's show requires.

01:10:16.000 --> 01:10:25.999
Feel it. Do not try to understand--enjoy
it. Bite, chew, taste, and enjoy.

01:10:26.000 --> 01:10:26.999
What you see is all there is. Just enjoy it.

01:10:27.000 --> 01:10:36.999
Enjoy it and--what are these socks?

01:10:37.000 --> 01:10:43.999
Enough! Tofu Knight, I shall defeat you.

01:10:44.000 --> 01:10:54.999
At last I understand the system. In the morning it's
'gisang'--getting up--but now I'm a 'gisa,' a knight.

01:10:55.000 --> 01:10:59.999
Understood.

01:11:00.000 --> 01:11:02.999
Confirm round one. Press it.

01:11:03.000 --> 01:11:08.999
Okay, press it. --I did.
--Not the right one. There.

01:11:09.000 --> 01:11:17.999
You have right and left
reversed. --It matters not.

01:11:18.000 --> 01:11:26.999
Melatonin Knight, dining at the
knights' diner. Tofu--delicious.

01:11:27.000 --> 01:11:33.999
You're quite fierce. Meat is good. Press okay.

01:11:34.000 --> 01:11:40.999
Ready. You're charging in on sheer momentum.

01:11:41.000 --> 01:11:47.999
Use your momentum! Block!
You're truly terrible at this.

01:11:48.000 --> 01:11:54.999
I shall defend for the fallen
knight. Let me be your black knight.

01:11:55.000 --> 01:12:03.999
We meet again on a narrow bridge. I want
to fall asleep again, but I shall resist.

01:12:04.000 --> 01:12:10.999
One more match. I shall face you as Yejun.

01:12:11.000 --> 01:12:18.999
Feel it. Simply feel it. Feel round one.

01:12:19.000 --> 01:12:33.999
Ready--begin.

01:12:34.000 --> 01:12:41.999
Almost there! Almost there!

01:12:42.000 --> 01:12:50.999
There it is! We're almost there!

01:12:51.000 --> 01:12:59.999
Almost there! One win--we're nearly there!

01:13:00.000 --> 01:13:07.999
I won! I won by half a beat! I really won!

01:13:08.000 --> 01:13:16.999
I won. That was not easy.

01:13:17.000 --> 01:13:30.999
He has awakened. Touch gloves. Win!

01:13:31.000 --> 01:13:35.999
I don't care who wins now.

01:13:36.000 --> 01:13:43.999
The head! The head! Can you withstand this?

01:13:44.000 --> 01:13:51.999
Impressive. That's it.

01:13:52.000 --> 01:13:53.999
There's a third round too?

01:13:54.000 --> 01:14:01.999
Must we play all three? The
dual-wielder has arrived.

01:14:02.000 --> 01:14:09.999
The head! When you see an
opening, strike from the side.

01:14:10.000 --> 01:14:18.999
The head! How impressive.

01:14:19.000 --> 01:14:26.999
Serve me. --Serve you? Why would I?

01:14:27.000 --> 01:14:35.999
I'm number one! At last we can move on.

01:14:36.000 --> 01:14:41.999
We felt plenty. We finally got the
okay. Thank you. What comes next?

01:14:42.000 --> 01:14:46.999
Was that enough material? --It
was delicious. --Was it? --Very.

01:14:47.000 --> 01:14:57.999
My shoulders hurt. What
is next? Tell us quickly.

01:14:58.000 --> 01:15:05.999
We need a demonstration before
we can do it. Show us the demo.

01:15:06.000 --> 01:15:15.999
There's no cue. Something went wrong. There--nice.
We've fought with swords, but isn't that violent?

01:15:16.000 --> 01:15:19.999
Noah posted on Weverse.

01:15:20.000 --> 01:15:26.999
'This is a historical drama--you call
this romance fantasy? Why am I involved?'

01:15:27.000 --> 01:15:34.999
Noah, you taught us plenty, but you're no
different. Just feel it. That's today's theme.

01:15:35.000 --> 01:15:42.999
Noah, on Thursday you too will
become a romance-fantasy character.

01:15:43.000 --> 01:15:51.999
You cannot escape. You will become a knight too.
Look forward to dining at the knights' diner.

01:15:52.000 --> 01:15:54.999
The melatonin will make you sleepy too.

01:15:55.000 --> 01:15:58.999
You will join the Order of
Melatonin. You are growing sleepy.

01:15:59.000 --> 01:16:05.999
We cannot settle everything through
sword fighting alone. --No, we cannot.

01:16:06.000 --> 01:16:12.999
We shall compete again by showing PLLI our
affectionate sides and winning her heart.

01:16:13.000 --> 01:16:19.999
Bring in the selfie camera. Come closer.

01:16:20.000 --> 01:16:26.999
The head, the head!

01:16:27.000 --> 01:16:32.999
We have prepared some truly sweet lines.
--Is this the language of romance?

01:16:33.000 --> 01:16:40.999
Let us read them. Is this another competition?

01:16:41.000 --> 01:16:46.999
It is a competition. Everything
is a competition today. --Okay.

01:16:47.000 --> 01:16:48.999
Very well. I shall go first.

01:16:49.000 --> 01:16:55.999
This isn't easy. Move slightly
sideways so I can see my opponent.

01:16:56.000 --> 01:17:00.999
Now recite it with feeling.

01:17:01.000 --> 01:17:07.999
PLLI, my legs feel weak... Legs...

01:17:08.000 --> 01:17:14.999
Why do you wander through my mind every night?

01:17:15.000 --> 01:17:21.999
You cannot escape either. Hurry and do yours.

01:17:22.000 --> 01:17:30.999
PLLI, what do you ride when you go home?

01:17:31.000 --> 01:17:37.999
I'm riding the road to romance with PLLI.

01:17:38.000 --> 01:17:45.999
Next. Do not stare blankly.

01:17:46.000 --> 01:17:54.999
Stand aside, PLLI.

01:17:55.000 --> 01:18:03.999
Today isn't easy. Did you take too much melatonin?
--Just feel it. I'm about to fall asleep.

01:18:04.000 --> 01:18:12.999
You may sleep, PLLI. Just enjoy it--and
please forget what you remember.

01:18:13.000 --> 01:18:15.999
PLLI, there's still time. At
least for today--all right.

01:18:16.000 --> 01:18:17.999
He's drifting off again. --I'm back, I'm back.

01:18:18.000 --> 01:18:26.999
At least for today... no.

01:18:27.000 --> 01:18:37.999
Stand aside. I thought you
were kind, but you aren't.

01:18:38.000 --> 01:18:46.999
Come to rest safely in my heart.

01:18:47.000 --> 01:18:55.999
You're trying hard. Draw your sword.
Was that worth a hundred calories?

01:18:56.000 --> 01:19:02.999
We must see the reaction. Let us
read the comments. PLLI is crying.

01:19:03.000 --> 01:19:10.999
Let's see whether PLLI understands
this particular sensibility.

01:19:11.000 --> 01:19:18.999
Even if you don't understand, don't
leave. Crazy--this love is crazy.

01:19:19.000 --> 01:19:27.999
The response is good. They like it.

01:19:28.000 --> 01:19:34.999
We are affectionate. Do you know who I am?

01:19:35.000 --> 01:19:42.999
Do you know who I am? The comments
contain nothing but laughter.

01:19:43.000 --> 01:19:45.999
Thank you for laughing.

01:19:46.000 --> 01:19:52.999
Bring the camera back in. --Why?

01:19:53.000 --> 01:20:05.999
You said you had one more thing prepared.
--There's more? I have something to say.

01:20:06.000 --> 01:20:10.999
I am a genius--the luckiest man under heaven.

01:20:11.000 --> 01:20:18.999
Because someone as lovely as PLLI is cheering
for me. Draw your sword--let's see the reaction.

01:20:19.000 --> 01:20:34.999
This one isn't easy. Must I really do it?

01:20:35.000 --> 01:20:42.999
I'll count you in. One, two, three, four!

01:20:43.000 --> 01:20:48.999
I am a genius--the luckiest man under heaven...

01:20:49.000 --> 01:20:59.999
...because someone as lovely
as PLLI is cheering for me.

01:21:00.000 --> 01:21:06.999
Honestly, I'm feeling a
little dizzy. Is it only me?

01:21:07.000 --> 01:21:14.999
Who are you? What is this? Please air
out the room. There's no oxygen in here.

01:21:15.000 --> 01:21:16.999
We are short of oxygen.

01:21:17.000 --> 01:21:24.999
I suddenly feel dizzy. Let's check the
response. This isn't easy for anyone.

01:21:25.000 --> 01:21:31.999
Not easy at all. It doesn't
look easy for PLLI either.

01:21:32.000 --> 01:21:37.999
You all came prepared to endure today's
show, right? --I want to leave.

01:21:38.000 --> 01:21:42.999
I want to go home.

01:21:43.000 --> 01:21:48.999
Sorry. Today is rather
difficult. Brace yourselves.

01:21:49.000 --> 01:21:57.999
Silence. This time we're going to
flirt. --Wasn't that what we just did?

01:21:58.000 --> 01:22:01.999
Those were sweet lines. Now
we're doing something different.

01:22:02.000 --> 01:22:08.999
They certainly were sweet. So it isn't flirting?

01:22:09.000 --> 01:22:11.999
Apparently we've prepared a
test of our attentiveness.

01:22:12.000 --> 01:22:16.999
Was it all decided already? --They
prepared several questions for us.

01:22:17.000 --> 01:22:24.999
Answer each one appropriately. Even
if a blade is held to my throat...

01:22:25.000 --> 01:22:33.999
...I shall answer to the very end. This is the
attentiveness section. They say to sit down.

01:22:34.000 --> 01:22:36.999
Take a seat.

01:22:37.000 --> 01:22:44.999
What is this? How very high-tech.

01:22:45.000 --> 01:22:48.999
What's this? The lights are sparkling.

01:22:49.000 --> 01:22:57.999
Won't it turn off? There, it worked.

01:22:58.000 --> 01:22:58.999
There. --No, it still won't turn off.

01:22:59.000 --> 01:23:07.999
This is not easy. I didn't drink
my yogurt today, so tonight...

01:23:08.000 --> 01:23:11.999
...is the sort of late night
that makes me long for yogurt.

01:23:12.000 --> 01:23:15.999
Now for the attentiveness section.

01:23:16.000 --> 01:23:19.999
I'll ask the first question.

01:23:20.000 --> 01:23:26.999
'Lady PLLI...' --What did you call her?
--I'm only reading what's written.

01:23:27.000 --> 01:23:35.999
Pronounce it again. 'Lady PLLI
suddenly says she likes someone else.'

01:23:36.000 --> 01:23:42.999
'How would you respond?' --I
would cut him down immediately.

01:23:43.000 --> 01:23:51.999
What an excellent solution. --I
would remove him from the picture.

01:23:52.000 --> 01:23:56.999
How would you respond?

01:23:57.000 --> 01:24:04.999
Does the lady have children?

01:24:05.000 --> 01:24:09.999
Me? I will not waste words.

01:24:10.000 --> 01:24:20.999
You are very direct. --My lady, I
love you. Stay by my side forever.

01:24:21.000 --> 01:24:24.999
I swear it for all my life.

01:24:25.000 --> 01:24:30.999
How can I follow something so
powerful? What am I meant to do?

01:24:31.000 --> 01:24:42.999
What will you do? As the last
one, please answer responsibly.

01:24:43.000 --> 01:24:51.999
This is my answer: 'You like someone else?'

01:24:52.000 --> 01:24:59.999
Put me full-screen. 'You
like someone else? Then go.'

01:25:00.000 --> 01:25:05.999
Go. I nearly laughed.

01:25:06.000 --> 01:25:14.999
How can you laugh in such a serious
situation? Now for the second question.

01:25:15.000 --> 01:25:22.999
You are unqualified as a knight.
Improve yourself. Read the second one.

01:25:23.000 --> 01:25:32.999
'While on a tender date with Lady PLLI, she
falls and is too embarrassed to get up.'

01:25:33.000 --> 01:25:38.999
'What would you do?' --I would cut
down every stone that made PLLI fall.

01:25:39.000 --> 01:25:42.999
I'll go next. Don't try too hard, or
you'll leave me with nothing to do.

01:25:43.000 --> 01:25:47.999
Give me something to work with. Help me out.

01:25:48.000 --> 01:25:54.999
PLLI has fallen and is too
embarrassed to get up.

01:25:55.000 --> 01:26:03.999
This is what I would do. Give me the
full screen. Please wait a moment.

01:26:04.000 --> 01:26:12.999
I would join her down there.

01:26:13.000 --> 01:26:20.999
I would share her embarrassment, joy, and
sorrow. Ah, my microphone is showing.

01:26:21.000 --> 01:26:21.999
You had a microphone?

01:26:22.000 --> 01:26:30.999
My expression looks strange too.
Please wait. Today really isn't easy.

01:26:31.000 --> 01:26:37.999
Today simply isn't easy. --But our love
will never grow cold. --All right.

01:26:38.000 --> 01:26:43.999
All right.

01:26:44.000 --> 01:26:50.999
Switch it back. This is
where I truly begin--wait.

01:26:51.000 --> 01:26:53.999
Do not go anywhere.

01:26:54.000 --> 01:27:01.999
Don't leave. Everyone watching, please bear
with us. We aren't normally like this.

01:27:02.000 --> 01:27:03.999
Do not leave us.

01:27:04.000 --> 01:27:11.999
Wait just a little longer and we'll give
you an even bigger laugh. Stand by.

01:27:12.000 --> 01:27:12.999
All right.

01:27:13.000 --> 01:27:16.999
She fell. What will you do?

01:27:17.000 --> 01:27:25.999
I'll go. PLLI, please wait a moment.

01:27:26.000 --> 01:27:33.999
I can't move. There.

01:27:34.000 --> 01:27:40.999
I'll show you. PLLI has fallen.

01:27:41.000 --> 01:27:45.999
She fell. Why do you keep
throwing away your sword?

01:27:46.000 --> 01:27:51.999
Are you sweeping the floor?

01:27:52.000 --> 01:27:54.999
Ah, you're using the
floor-sweeping sword technique.

01:27:55.000 --> 01:28:01.999
I was taught that comedy is built
on repetition. --Repetition indeed.

01:28:02.000 --> 01:28:07.999
It turned on again. You're doing an
excellent job repeating the joke.

01:28:08.000 --> 01:28:15.999
Where did you buy this? I
think you were scammed.

01:28:16.000 --> 01:28:18.999
It switches on whenever it pleases.

01:28:19.000 --> 01:28:22.999
Oh? There, I fixed it.

01:28:23.000 --> 01:28:29.999
I showed it properly, didn't I? --You did.

01:28:30.000 --> 01:28:37.999
We look like fools. --I would fall
with her and share the embarrassment.

01:28:38.000 --> 01:28:40.999
That does have merit.

01:28:41.000 --> 01:28:51.999
Read the third question. 'Lady PLLI's parents
strongly oppose your relationship. What do you do?'

01:28:52.000 --> 01:28:54.999
I shall become their son-in-law.

01:28:55.000 --> 01:29:01.999
I wish to marry your daughter. I would
respectfully ask their permission.

01:29:02.000 --> 01:29:11.999
Well done. What will you do first? This
keeps turning on--how do I stop it?

01:29:12.000 --> 01:29:16.999
We can proceed without it.
Just feel it. --Understood.

01:29:17.000 --> 01:29:21.999
I'll go first. I'll give you time to think.

01:29:22.000 --> 01:29:33.999
Dear parents--it blocked me again.
Wait, I think this is going to break.

01:29:34.000 --> 01:29:40.999
Dear parents... You suddenly
hate this man from Seoul.

01:29:41.000 --> 01:29:47.999
Again? That was a surprise
attack. How much do you hate me?

01:29:48.000 --> 01:29:59.999
The third question is rather
daunting. There's a lot of pressure.

01:30:00.000 --> 01:30:09.999
Esteemed parents...

01:30:10.000 --> 01:30:15.999
You startled me.

01:30:16.000 --> 01:30:23.999
I possess nothing but...

01:30:24.000 --> 01:30:34.999
...my love for your daughter, but as a knight I
shall treat her to knights' diner meals for life.

01:30:35.000 --> 01:30:41.999
Please permit us to marry. --That was good.

01:30:42.000 --> 01:30:49.999
Honestly, the pace dragged. Do it again. Have
you only hosted live shows for a day or two?

01:30:50.000 --> 01:30:53.999
Is that what you were taught?
Even I can't rescue this segment.

01:30:54.000 --> 01:31:03.999
Dear parents, I dislike you--

01:31:04.000 --> 01:31:06.999
I've run out of ideas.
Sorry, I have nothing left.

01:31:07.000 --> 01:31:18.999
As a fellow knight, I understand. Parents,
take this sword and strike me down.

01:31:19.000 --> 01:31:25.999
Let's move on. Please, move on.

01:31:26.000 --> 01:31:34.999
'Before a ball, Lady PLLI opens her wardrobe
and finds no suitable dress. What do you do?'

01:31:35.000 --> 01:31:41.999
I shall make one for her. --Make it?

01:31:42.000 --> 01:31:49.999
I shall make one too. --You're making it
yourselves? --I will personally design it.

01:31:50.000 --> 01:31:58.999
Then let us design one.

01:31:59.000 --> 01:32:04.999
Preparation will take a moment. How
long must we keep speaking this way?

01:32:05.000 --> 01:32:13.999
We chose the wrong concept. We have thirty minutes
left, but with these swords, we cannot drop the voice.

01:32:14.000 --> 01:32:20.999
Endure it for thirty minutes. We've made enough
material for Shorts. This is a transition.

01:32:21.000 --> 01:32:29.999
So that was the button. Mine isn't
appearing. I'll show you how it's done.

01:32:30.000 --> 01:32:34.999
Take a seat. Where should we sit?

01:32:35.000 --> 01:32:42.999
There--the chairs were here. Move
downstream. So I was downstream.

01:32:43.000 --> 01:32:49.999
Sorry, I thought I was upstream,
but apparently I was downstream.

01:32:50.000 --> 01:32:56.999
I need a drink of water. Now we
shall design the dresses ourselves.

01:32:57.000 --> 01:33:04.999
Let's begin what we've prepared.

01:33:05.000 --> 01:33:11.999
Express it as a drawing. Design the dress.

01:33:12.000 --> 01:33:13.999
Understood.

01:33:14.000 --> 01:33:30.999
I shall dress PLLI in a magnificent gown.

01:33:31.000 --> 01:33:35.999
The audio is a little empty.
Please fill the silence.

01:33:36.000 --> 01:33:40.999
Keep drawing with your hand, but
don't let your mouth rest either.

01:33:41.000 --> 01:33:49.999
My hands may rest, but my mouth shall work.
I cannot bring myself to laugh right now.

01:33:50.000 --> 01:34:02.999
Laugh. Laugh.

01:34:03.000 --> 01:34:11.999
[Singing in English]

01:34:12.000 --> 01:34:26.999
We're taking this all the way today.

01:34:27.000 --> 01:34:35.999
[Singing in English]

01:34:36.000 --> 01:35:09.999
[Singing in English]

01:35:10.000 --> 01:35:12.999
Is everyone's work progressing
well? --Of course.

01:35:13.000 --> 01:35:33.999
An extraordinary picture is taking shape.

01:35:34.000 --> 01:35:53.999
There were colors available?

01:35:54.000 --> 01:36:03.999
This isn't easy. I'm considering the
brand. Which brand does PLLI like?

01:36:04.000 --> 01:36:11.999
PLLI's favorite brand? I must
think about that. The PLAVE brand.

01:36:12.000 --> 01:36:16.999
As expected of our leader. That was good.

01:36:17.000 --> 01:36:23.999
[Singing in English]

01:36:24.000 --> 01:36:31.999
[Singing in English]

01:36:32.000 --> 01:36:41.999
[Singing in English]

01:36:42.000 --> 01:36:42.999
I don't even know how to spell it.

01:36:43.000 --> 01:36:48.999
[Singing in English] I
dressed her in Louis Vuitton.

01:36:49.000 --> 01:37:05.999
So you'll dress her in something
expensive. [Singing in English]

01:37:06.000 --> 01:37:14.999
[Singing in English]

01:37:15.000 --> 01:37:24.999
You're choosing Nike, then. The
shoes are... [Singing in English]

01:37:25.000 --> 01:37:32.999
What does that logo look like? No--what is this?

01:37:33.000 --> 01:37:41.999
What's happening? How do I use this pen again?

01:37:42.000 --> 01:37:53.999
The pen is acting up. You
cannot see my drawing yet.

01:37:54.000 --> 01:38:06.999
I'm drawing PLLI beautifully.
Please wait a little longer.

01:38:07.000 --> 01:38:12.999
[Singing in English]

01:38:13.000 --> 01:38:34.999
[Singing in English]

01:38:35.000 --> 01:38:46.999
Where are the colors?

01:38:47.000 --> 01:38:51.999
It's almost finished. Please
wait just a little longer.

01:38:52.000 --> 01:39:01.999
Simply feel it today. I can't alter the face.

01:39:02.000 --> 01:39:18.999
You can't? What a pity.

01:39:19.000 --> 01:39:27.999
Are you using primary colors?

01:39:28.000 --> 01:39:43.999
Hello there.

01:39:44.000 --> 01:39:56.999
This isn't easy. I shall dye
her hair. Truly not easy.

01:39:57.000 --> 01:40:04.999
I'm done. I don't quite know how to
color this app. This is difficult.

01:40:05.000 --> 01:40:18.999
Press it. The world of art is not an easy one.

01:40:19.000 --> 01:40:32.999
Yejun, are you all right?
--Everything looks good.

01:40:33.000 --> 01:40:39.999
PLLI, do you like sagging fashion? If
you wish, I shall dress you that way.

01:40:40.000 --> 01:41:17.999
Would that be all right? Is
sagging in fashion these days?

01:41:18.000 --> 01:41:28.999
I'm almost finished. What sort of clothes
does one wear for sagging fashion?

01:41:29.000 --> 01:41:35.999
Sorry. --Apologize properly.

01:41:36.000 --> 01:41:49.999
I'm finished. --I'm nearly
done too. Please wait.

01:41:50.000 --> 01:42:02.999
Shouldn't the hair have a
little more volume? Good.

01:42:03.000 --> 01:42:10.999
Wait. I'll add a yellow accent.
You like Calvin Klein, don't you?

01:42:11.000 --> 01:42:19.999
Understood. I have dressed you in Calvin Klein.

01:42:20.000 --> 01:42:50.999
I'm practically finished.
Perfect. Where can I find yellow?

01:42:51.000 --> 01:42:57.999
Done.

01:42:58.000 --> 01:43:07.999
I've finished everything. This
is enough. --I'm done too.

01:43:08.000 --> 01:43:12.999
Why did you create a monster?
--A monster? How dare you!

01:43:13.000 --> 01:43:24.999
Thank you. I think we're nearly finished.

01:43:25.000 --> 01:43:29.999
The PLLI that Eunho-hyung
drew is a boss monster.

01:43:30.000 --> 01:43:33.999
She looks like the final boss
you must defeat in a game.

01:43:34.000 --> 01:43:42.999
I may have given her see-through bangs by mistake.
I shall present them to her. Are you done?

01:43:43.000 --> 01:43:48.999
Let us inspect them. Please explain your design.

01:43:49.000 --> 01:44:00.999
Mine seems the most ordinary, so I'll go
first. I think this picture speaks for itself.

01:44:01.000 --> 01:44:07.999
This is my wife. --Your wife?

01:44:08.000 --> 01:44:15.999
She is very graceful, upright in character,
and a person of excellent virtue.

01:44:16.000 --> 01:44:21.999
This is my wife. I drew a portrait of her.

01:44:22.000 --> 01:44:28.999
At home, my wife often wears hanbok.

01:44:29.000 --> 01:44:36.999
Hanbok is refined, comfortable,
and well ventilated.

01:44:37.000 --> 01:44:44.999
So I dressed her in hanbok. Her hair has the
silky shine of an Elastine advertisement.

01:44:45.000 --> 01:44:53.999
I expressed her smooth, healthy hair
swept to one side. Isn't she beautiful?

01:44:54.000 --> 01:44:56.999
It suits her extremely well.
Her beauty is outstanding.

01:44:57.000 --> 01:45:03.999
And to complete her fashionable
look, I added yellow shoes.

01:45:04.000 --> 01:45:12.999
That concludes my presentation. Thank you.

01:45:13.000 --> 01:45:21.999
Next. What sort of creature is this?

01:45:22.000 --> 01:45:22.999
My wife.

01:45:23.000 --> 01:45:26.999
Your... wife?

01:45:27.000 --> 01:45:33.999
This is my wife, who loves primary colors.
She seems to have exercised a great deal.

01:45:34.000 --> 01:45:41.999
No, that's just how the clothes look. --They look
uncomfortable. Are those pimples on her head?

01:45:42.000 --> 01:45:45.999
They are not pimples. Do not squeeze them.

01:45:46.000 --> 01:45:53.999
You misunderstood. She dyed her
hair pink. That's hair--not a nose.

01:45:54.000 --> 01:46:01.999
Hair? It looks as if Shin-chan's
mother hit her twice. --It is hair.

01:46:02.000 --> 01:46:05.999
My wife has beautifully curled
hair. --So those were curls.

01:46:06.000 --> 01:46:13.999
She likes very comfortable clothing. --It looks
uncomfortable to anyone. --No, it is comfortable.

01:46:14.000 --> 01:46:17.999
You chose yellow as well. --Yellow indeed.

01:46:18.000 --> 01:46:24.999
We have something in common:
we both chose yellow shoes.

01:46:25.000 --> 01:46:34.999
My beautiful yellow shoes are
lovely. --Why are the trousers blue?

01:46:35.000 --> 01:46:36.999
Must I not ask? --I was simply curious.

01:46:37.000 --> 01:46:39.999
I chose blue because I like it.

01:46:40.000 --> 01:46:48.999
A person like the sea, then. And this is
the sagging fashion? --Yes, Calvin Klein.

01:46:49.000 --> 01:46:50.999
I'm sorry, but it isn't
called that. It's 'sagging.'

01:46:51.000 --> 01:46:59.999
Are you genuinely asking what
sagging fashion is? Are you serious?

01:47:00.000 --> 01:47:09.999
You truly don't know? Hosting a
show with this fellow is not easy.

01:47:10.000 --> 01:47:17.999
Remember this: besides sagging, there
are standard fit, slim fit, bootcut...

01:47:18.000 --> 01:47:23.999
...and regular fit. Don't you know those? --No.

01:47:24.000 --> 01:47:25.999
That's right.

01:47:26.000 --> 01:47:33.999
Look up wide fit after the show.
--Understood. Now explain your design.

01:47:34.000 --> 01:47:42.999
Let us meet the final boss. I shall
explain her. She is holding a sickle too.

01:47:43.000 --> 01:47:50.999
My muse. --Sorry, but is
the hair actually finished?

01:47:51.000 --> 01:47:59.999
I expressed sagging through her hair too. I added
highlighted streaks--those are fashionable.

01:48:00.000 --> 01:48:07.999
It is fashionable sagging style.
And these are vintage earrings.

01:48:08.000 --> 01:48:13.999
Earrings? What did you think they were? --Ramen.

01:48:14.000 --> 01:48:17.999
It looks as if ramen was poured
over her. Ramen is yellow.

01:48:18.000 --> 01:48:22.999
So yellow is the common thread again.

01:48:23.000 --> 01:48:29.999
In any case, I styled the hair and
accessories around this sagging concept.

01:48:30.000 --> 01:48:33.999
That isn't how the word is
used. --This is driving me mad.

01:48:34.000 --> 01:48:40.999
Then I shall call it 'new fashion'
instead--brand-new fashion.

01:48:41.000 --> 01:48:44.999
Brand-new, not secondhand. --Understood.

01:48:45.000 --> 01:48:52.999
This is a hairpin. --A pin? --It's
gold. --Her scalp looks painful.

01:48:53.000 --> 01:48:54.999
It does not hurt.

01:48:55.000 --> 01:49:02.999
And at the front, she has see-through
bangs. --So she does have hair.

01:49:03.000 --> 01:49:06.999
See-through bangs. This isn't sagging
fashion; it's 'baby' fashion.

01:49:07.000 --> 01:49:09.999
Baby fashion? --Yes, like a
child who hasn't grown up yet.

01:49:10.000 --> 01:49:15.999
My muse sometimes has a childlike
quality too. That is one of her charms.

01:49:16.000 --> 01:49:23.999
Those see-through bangs look almost
newborn. --That is fashion. Just feel it.

01:49:24.000 --> 01:49:24.999
Baby fashion.

01:49:25.000 --> 01:49:32.999
Just feel it. And here I expressed
the clavicles. --Her clavicles?

01:49:33.000 --> 01:49:38.999
They're rather high. --Aren't
those muscles? Or her vocal cords?

01:49:39.000 --> 01:49:46.999
With a dress, the clavicles are a focal point.
I gave her perfectly straight clavicles.

01:49:47.000 --> 01:49:55.999
And here I wrote a message telling
everyone to stay tuned to PLAVE's channel.

01:49:56.000 --> 01:50:03.999
Channel, not Chanel. It means,
'Keep the channel here.'

01:50:04.000 --> 01:50:12.999
It asks people to stay tuned to PLAVE's
YouTube channel. Is your wife left-handed?

01:50:13.000 --> 01:50:13.999
She is not my wife. She is my muse.

01:50:14.000 --> 01:50:20.999
My muse is left-handed, so the muscles
in her left arm are more developed.

01:50:21.000 --> 01:50:29.999
From all the rowing? She has a sickle in
this hand--what is in the other, a hammer?

01:50:30.000 --> 01:50:33.999
I could not fully express that part in
the drawing. There is a story behind it.

01:50:34.000 --> 01:50:41.999
If I drew what she held in her right hand, we
couldn't broadcast it. --It would fail review?

01:50:42.000 --> 01:50:42.999
Content review, indeed.

01:50:43.000 --> 01:50:50.999
In any case, I completed my muse's dress
in this elegant fashion. --It's strange.

01:50:51.000 --> 01:50:53.999
Understood.

01:50:54.000 --> 01:51:00.999
PLLI, which dress would you most like to
wear? I'm fairly sure it isn't this one.

01:51:01.000 --> 01:51:03.999
Why not?

01:51:04.000 --> 01:51:11.999
That one belongs on a cartoon channel.
--Take my hand and come with me.

01:51:12.000 --> 01:51:16.999
And that one--I feel as though
I've seen it somewhere before.

01:51:17.000 --> 01:51:20.999
This is difficult. I never
thought to draw a neck.

01:51:21.000 --> 01:51:28.999
There was an old game called 'Dad 'n
Me.' She resembles a character from it.

01:51:29.000 --> 01:51:37.999
This one somehow feels unsafe to
wear. PLLI, which would you choose?

01:51:38.000 --> 01:51:46.999
They're saying, 'I won't go.' Must they
choose? Eunho seems to be getting many votes.

01:51:47.000 --> 01:51:50.999
You'd have to carry both a sickle and
a hammer. Would that be all right?

01:51:51.000 --> 01:51:59.999
You also need the see-through bangs and a
light implanted in the top of your head.

01:52:00.000 --> 01:52:08.999
Not merely attached--implanted. That would hurt. They
say they'll stay home because their wardrobe is full.

01:52:09.000 --> 01:52:16.999
Understood. If choosing is too difficult, we shall
simply move on. We have designed our dresses.

01:52:17.000 --> 01:52:24.999
There is a script we need
to read. I shall read it.

01:52:25.000 --> 01:52:32.999
Just in case: please never wear these outfits to
the concert. --I wouldn't, even if you asked.

01:52:33.000 --> 01:52:39.999
It may be hot outdoors, uncomfortable, and the sickle
or hammer could be heavy. --Hammers are heavy.

01:52:40.000 --> 01:52:46.999
We shall decide on a nice concert dress
code separately. We mention this because...

01:52:47.000 --> 01:52:53.999
...the company was genuinely worried PLLI
might come dressed according to our drawings.

01:52:54.000 --> 01:53:01.999
They insisted we say this. Surely nobody
would wear that. --If you can, give it a try.

01:53:02.000 --> 01:53:07.999
We have faith. Just feel it.

01:53:08.000 --> 01:53:15.999
This may sound presumptuous, but my
dancing has improved greatly lately.

01:53:16.000 --> 01:53:19.999
Then you must show us. --A royal command.

01:53:20.000 --> 01:53:28.999
Please choose which one of us
you most want to dance with.

01:53:29.000 --> 01:53:34.999
You have chosen. I didn't expect you
to have a clear favorite among us.

01:53:35.000 --> 01:53:40.999
Then Yejun goes first. Go on, Yejun.

01:53:41.000 --> 01:53:43.999
Begin. A violin has been prepared.

01:53:44.000 --> 01:53:50.999
Even a violin? How beautiful.
Please display your skill.

01:53:51.000 --> 01:54:02.999
Wait a moment.

01:54:03.000 --> 01:54:09.999
[Violin playing and singing]

01:54:10.000 --> 01:54:18.999
You are meant to dance. Why are
you looking at somebody else?

01:54:19.000 --> 01:54:44.999
How am I supposed to play violin to
this music? Make the sound for me.

01:54:45.000 --> 01:54:48.999
[Violin playing]

01:54:49.000 --> 01:54:59.999
[Singing] I'll simply close
my eyes and continue.

01:55:00.000 --> 01:55:07.999
[Singing]

01:55:08.000 --> 01:55:19.999
[Singing] Is this a song request?

01:55:20.000 --> 01:55:27.999
How long are we going to keep doing this?

01:55:28.000 --> 01:55:32.999
And that brings it to an end.

01:55:33.000 --> 01:55:39.999
I think it is time to show our secret weapons.
--More secret weapons? How far will this go?

01:55:40.000 --> 01:55:47.999
How much more will you show? Everyone,
reveal your secret weapons. --What weapon?

01:55:48.000 --> 01:55:53.999
I shall go first. I prepared a dance.

01:55:54.000 --> 01:56:01.999
Melt PLLI's hearts. Music, please.

01:56:02.000 --> 01:56:25.999
Please begin.

01:56:26.000 --> 01:56:27.999
How was my special move?

01:56:28.000 --> 01:56:35.999
Then I shall dance while acting
cute. --You're adding aegyo too?

01:56:36.000 --> 01:56:39.999
I'm going to do 'Bad.' --Without accompaniment?

01:56:40.000 --> 01:56:44.999
You're doing 'Bad' a
cappella? Only the fox part?

01:56:45.000 --> 01:56:55.999
[Singing]

01:56:56.000 --> 01:57:11.999
I think I'm having some
kind of episode. I'm sorry.

01:57:12.000 --> 01:57:14.999
I love you, senior. I love you.

01:57:15.000 --> 01:57:15.999
I'm sorry.

01:57:16.000 --> 01:57:25.999
Only your special move remains. --We
cannot start repeating things now.

01:57:26.000 --> 01:57:29.999
Is that how you learned to host a
live? Stop it. This isn't right.

01:57:30.000 --> 01:57:37.999
Stop. We've been doing this
for four years. Are you ready?

01:57:38.000 --> 01:57:43.999
Music, please. --There's more music?

01:57:44.000 --> 01:57:47.999
They can't play anything unless
you tell them what music you want.

01:57:48.000 --> 01:57:54.999
I didn't arrange music for my dance in advance.
I shall walk the same path as my muse.

01:57:55.000 --> 01:57:56.999
Surely not 'Bad' again? --It is 'Bad.'

01:57:57.000 --> 01:58:02.999
We just told you not to repeat it. --That earlier
repetition was a mistake. I'm staying true to the lyrics.

01:58:03.000 --> 01:58:05.999
You mean true to the title. This is truly bad.

01:58:06.000 --> 01:58:19.999
Let's see it, then. Show us.

01:58:20.000 --> 01:58:32.999
The beat seems slightly off.

01:58:33.000 --> 01:58:37.999
How are you going to take
responsibility for this situation?

01:58:38.000 --> 01:58:43.999
What was your intention? I don't
know why I did that either.

01:58:44.000 --> 01:58:52.999
Shall all three of us try
it? I have no idea anymore.

01:58:53.000 --> 01:58:59.999
I give up on understanding today.
Music, please. Just feel it.

01:59:00.000 --> 01:59:33.999
Music, please.

01:59:34.000 --> 01:59:43.999
And that is enough.

01:59:44.000 --> 01:59:48.999
Good work. PLLI, what did you think?

01:59:49.000 --> 01:59:55.999
Move back a little and get settled.
Why are we sitting so low?

01:59:56.000 --> 02:00:00.999
Who set this so low? There, we're ready.

02:00:01.000 --> 02:00:09.999
Now, what if we finally
drop the role-play voices?

02:00:10.000 --> 02:00:14.999
Good idea. What do you think? --Let's do that.

02:00:15.000 --> 02:00:22.999
Great. For today's broadcast, we
made a tremendous effort for PLLI...

02:00:23.000 --> 02:00:30.999
...an effort to show you lots of
entertaining sides of ourselves.

02:00:31.000 --> 02:00:38.999
I'm curious what you thought of this rather
melatonin-like show. People are saying we worked hard.

02:00:39.000 --> 02:00:44.999
We're always ready to work hard for PLLI. It
was fun, wasn't it? Honestly, we had fun.

02:00:45.000 --> 02:00:48.999
I only hope too many people
didn't leave while watching.

02:00:49.000 --> 02:00:52.999
Please explain to everyone around you
that we aren't normally like this.

02:00:53.000 --> 02:00:54.999
PLLI says they have goosebumps. Why?

02:00:55.000 --> 02:00:59.999
I have them too. We all do.

02:01:00.000 --> 02:01:02.999
Today we delivered quite a
small--and precious--broadcast.

02:01:03.000 --> 02:01:10.999
It's already time to end. Shall we
first take our customary photo?

02:01:11.000 --> 02:01:25.999
Right. Let's have capture
time. Sit down together.

02:01:26.000 --> 02:01:33.999
I'll hold the violin.

02:01:34.000 --> 02:01:40.999
Take the picture, and I'll...

02:01:41.000 --> 02:01:53.999
Be careful. Please treasure this picture.

02:01:54.000 --> 02:02:00.999
Now that capture time is over, it is time
to choose today's highlight playlist song.

02:02:01.000 --> 02:02:08.999
For the romance-fantasy mood--and since
it was performed at the World Cup too...

02:02:09.000 --> 02:02:11.999
...how about BTS's 'Dynamite'?

02:02:12.000 --> 02:02:23.999
'Dynamite' sounds splendid. We shall end today's
show on an exciting note. Music, please.

02:02:24.000 --> 02:02:33.999
Must we do this part too? All right.

02:02:34.000 --> 02:02:39.999
This is driving me mad. We have to
join in too, don't we? --We do.

02:02:40.000 --> 02:03:01.999
Dance! Move! This remains
difficult right to the end.

02:03:02.000 --> 02:03:13.999
[BTS's 'Dynamite' plays]

02:03:14.000 --> 02:04:02.999
[BTS's 'Dynamite' plays]

02:04:03.000 --> 02:04:34.999
[BTS's 'Dynamite' plays]

02:04:35.000 --> 02:05:11.999
[BTS's 'Dynamite' plays]

02:05:12.000 --> 02:05:36.999
[BTS's 'Dynamite' plays]

02:05:37.000 --> 02:05:42.999
Thank you. Bye!
